00:56:12,635 --> 00:56:13,897
I got to go.

987
00:56:14,304 --> 00:56:19,298
Don't judge us too harshly, Pearl.

988
00:56:20,577 --> 00:56:27,346
There is more decency and kindness
and humanity

989
00:56:27,417 --> 00:56:29,885
in that building than I ever saw.

990
00:56:29,953 --> 00:56:30,977
I don't know.

991
00:56:31,087 --> 00:56:32,315
The truth is,

992
00:56:32,389 --> 00:56:38,259
you getting hired has been the most
exciting work-related event since,

993
00:56:38,395 --> 00:56:44,891
since Hickman Moody nailed his hand into
the desk with a pneumatic staple gun.

994
00:56:45,368 --> 00:56:48,963
I'm enjoying work because of you.

995
00:56:52,609 --> 00:56:54,372
Are you coming to work tomorrow?

996
00:57:13,630 --> 00:57:14,858
It'll never work.

997
00:57:15,799 --> 00:57:17,426
He is a vampire, and I'm not.

998
00:57:20,603 --> 00:57:23,003
Leave me alone.

999
00:57:42,592 --> 00:57:43,718
Otto.

1000
00:57:44,661 --> 00:57:48,256
Henry read me the riot act
over spilling my guts about the life

1001
00:57:48,331 --> 00:57:50,196
and using the back door to sneak out.

1002
00:57:51,134 --> 00:57:53,694
If we were beasts,
the solution would be obvious.

1003
00:57:54,070 --> 00:57:55,833
Make the problem disappear.

1004
00:57:56,973 --> 00:58:00,238
I guess I didn't want to admit
that option was still on the table.

1005
00:58:01,478 --> 00:58:05,312
This is going to go on your permanent
record, Otto. On your permanent record.

1006
00:58:07,917 --> 00:58:09,350
What if she tells somebody?

1007
00:58:09,419 --> 00:58:10,716
Who's she going to tell?

1008
00:58:10,787 --> 00:58:11,583
Friends?

1009
00:58:11,654 --> 00:58:13,349
She doesn't have friends,
she's anti-social.

1010
00:58:13,756 --> 00:58:14,154
Family.

1011
00:58:14,224 --> 00:58:15,191
She doesn't have family.

1012
00:58:15,325 --> 00:58:17,156
Her parents died, she has no siblings.

1013
00:58:17,994 --> 00:58:20,554
Otto,
how do you know all this about her?

1014
00:58:22,532 --> 00:58:23,590
I knew you were going to ask that.

1015
00:58:23,666 --> 00:58:26,863
Anyway, no decision could be
made until tomorrow morning,

1016
00:58:26,936 --> 00:58:31,373
when our problem either
showed up for work, or not.

1017
00:58:31,741 --> 00:58:34,141
Hey, what are you guys doing?

1018
00:58:34,644 --> 00:58:37,010
Oh, for God's sakes,
Dan, put on some undergarments.

1019
00:58:37,514 --> 00:58:39,004
I'm wearing one.

1020
00:58:39,382 --> 00:58:42,215
Come on, Dow, those are for ladies.

1021
00:58:42,552 --> 00:58:45,112
Oh, how right you are, my friend.

1022
00:58:52,562 --> 00:58:55,326
The next morning,
eight o'clock came and went.

1023
00:58:57,967 --> 00:58:59,457
So did eighty-thirty.

1024
00:59:00,169 --> 00:59:01,363
No Pearl.

1025
00:59:02,639 --> 00:59:04,539
There was no time to dwell on it.

1026
00:59:04,607 --> 00:59:06,905
Instead of looking for Rebecca
or the Nether Stone,

1027
00:59:07,110 --> 00:59:11,012
Henry asked me to host a babysitting
meeting to keep Turner occupied.

1028
00:59:11,581 --> 00:59:14,914
Sadly, it wasn't terribly different
from most meetings.

1029
00:59:15,485 --> 00:59:20,821
So ballpoint pens should be made
available in at least four colors?

1030
00:59:21,090 --> 00:59:22,819
That's a simple fix.

1031
00:59:23,092 --> 00:59:26,289
We need to go after
that low hanging fruit, people.

1032
00:59:26,362 --> 00:59:28,956
Waxy Dan,
can you take this action item?

1033
00:59:29,032 --> 00:59:30,556
Oh, I'll knock it out of the park,
Otto.

1034
00:59:30,767 --> 00:59:32,496
Sorry I'm late.

1035
00:59:34,203 --> 00:59:35,329
Morning, Pearl.

1036
00:59:36,005 --> 00:59:38,439
This meeting's been great.
I have to get to another one.

1037
00:59:41,778 --> 00:59:44,042
I always get asked
to pick the low hanging fruit.

1038
00:59:44,113 --> 00:59:46,581
Do you believe I'm capable of
picking the mid-level fruit?

1039
00:59:46,883 --> 00:59:50,751
Oh, hang on, uh, if I drew
this fruit quadrant thing right,

1040
00:59:50,820 --> 00:59:54,722
I don't think there can be
any mid-level fruit to pick.

1041
00:59:55,124 --> 00:59:59,117
It's true. Mid-level would require
a nine-square tic-tac-toe config.

1042
00:59:59,195 --> 01:00:00,253
People, please.

1043
01:00:00,396 --> 01:00:03,832
Let's not complicate
the strategic fruit maxim.

1044
01:00:04,133 --> 01:00:06,658
I was gosh-bustified
that she came back.

1045
01:00:07,904 --> 01:00:10,532
In an effort to establish a real home
for her at Berm-Tech,

1046
01:00:10,607 --> 01:00:13,838
we worked together to get rid
of all the Mike Yarrow stuff.

1047
01:00:15,278 --> 01:00:16,540
I got it.

1048
01:00:22,652 --> 01:00:25,212
But the thing
that I don't get is 'why? '

1049
01:00:26,489 --> 01:00:29,253
Why coop yourselves up
in here and hide?

1050
01:00:30,326 --> 01:00:35,161
I mean, shouldn't you be out
there being superheroes or something?

1051
01:00:36,165 --> 01:00:38,030
I mean, you're kind of immortal.

1052
01:00:39,202 --> 01:00:42,330
Don't you just think
that you're meant for something big?

1053
01:00:42,572 --> 01:00:45,905
Yeah. Sure, I mean,
I thought about it.

1054
01:00:47,110 --> 01:00:51,103
But eventually I came to the conclusion,
and it's one that we all share,

1055
01:00:51,814 --> 01:00:55,773
this gift is as impractical
as it can be.

1056
01:00:56,486 --> 01:00:58,351
It's like somebody
pulled a trick on us.

1057
01:00:59,088 --> 01:01:00,680
What? Like a curse?

1058
01:01:02,191 --> 01:01:05,718
Not so much a curse as a test.

1059
01:01:07,163 --> 01:01:08,494
Something to overcome.

1060
01:01:09,966 --> 01:01:10,933
It's our cross to bear.

1061
01:01:12,268 --> 01:01:14,361
We're just trying to
maintain our humanity.

1062
01:01:23,980 --> 01:01:25,181
What's this?

1063
01:01:25,181 --> 01:01:27,513
That's when we discovered
a huge piece of the puzzle.

1064
01:01:29,786 --> 01:01:31,310
Whoa, what's wrong?

1065
01:01:35,324 --> 01:01:38,054
Pearl, I'll be back in a few minutes.

1066
01:01:38,127 --> 01:01:39,754
Will you take this stuff
to the basement?

1067
01:01:40,563 --> 01:01:41,825
It's okay.

1068
01:01:58,581 --> 01:02:01,573
You're right.
It's definitely Chesnok Red.

1069
01:02:03,386 --> 01:02:04,910
How lethal is that stuff?

1070
01:02:04,987 --> 01:02:06,477
Oh, it'll kill you.

1071
01:02:12,061 --> 01:02:13,995
What about in smaller doses?

1072
01:02:15,098 --> 01:02:17,430
Like spread out over time?

1073
01:02:18,101 --> 01:02:19,932
It would certainly affect the organs.

1074
01:02:20,002 --> 01:02:23,372
The liver, the pancreas,
the intestines, both large and small.

1075
01:02:23,372 --> 01:02:25,897
The stomach, the kidneys,
most sexual organs.

1076
01:02:25,975 --> 01:02:28,603
And the brain would deteriorate
and begin to lose function.

1077
01:02:29,612 --> 01:02:31,842
Like the retardations.

1078
01:02:32,215 --> 01:02:34,945
"A MONTH AGO"
Precisely, way down.

1079
01:02:35,017 --> 01:02:37,383
Our projected figures for
June were based on aggregate cost...

1080
01:02:37,453 --> 01:02:40,479
See,
Turner used to be keen as a blade.

1081
01:02:41,257 --> 01:02:43,953
What's Mike Yarrow doing
in this managers meeting?

1082
01:02:44,227 --> 01:02:46,957
Sucking up.
In the vernacular of the times,

1083
01:02:47,029 --> 01:02:51,261
Mike was a dick.
A two-faced, kiss ass, toady.

1084
01:02:52,034 --> 01:02:52,659
Alright.

1085
01:02:52,735 --> 01:02:53,997
Let me top that off for you.

1086
01:02:54,070 --> 01:02:54,695
The glasses are...

1087
01:02:54,771 --> 01:02:55,795
No, don't worry.

1088
01:02:55,872 --> 01:02:56,964
No, I appreciate what you're trying...

1089
01:02:57,039 --> 01:02:58,529
I mean, continue. You were on a roll.

1090
01:02:58,708 --> 01:03:03,168
And, uh, let me say, that tie,
really compliments your eyes.

1091
01:03:03,246 --> 01:03:05,714
Now we know why Mike was always there.

1092
01:03:08,718 --> 01:03:11,346
I'm in now, I'm done with Rebecca.

1093
01:03:54,497 --> 01:03:56,192
Pearl!

1094
01:03:56,566 --> 01:03:57,692
You shouldn't be down here.

1095
01:03:59,569 --> 01:04:01,264
Dow, Dow...

1096
01:04:01,871 --> 01:04:02,997
Where's the fire, guys?

1097
01:04:03,072 --> 01:04:04,437
Do you still have Mike Yarrow's PC?

1098
01:04:04,507 --> 01:04:05,997
Yeah. It's right over there.

1099
01:04:06,075 --> 01:04:07,303
Alright, we need you to go through it.

1100
01:04:07,376 --> 01:04:09,139
Uh, the hard drive,
the email, everything,

1101
01:04:09,212 --> 01:04:13,376
see if you can find any hint
of a plot to, well, poison Turner.

1102
01:04:13,749 --> 01:04:14,943
Plot to poison Turner, huh?

1103
01:04:15,017 --> 01:04:16,075
How, how long will it take?

1104
01:04:17,553 --> 01:04:18,520
No telling, Otto.

1105
01:04:18,855 --> 01:04:20,186
A computer's not
a frigging mellon-baller.

1106
01:04:20,256 --> 01:04:21,917
I don't know
what surprised Bunyan more,

1107
01:04:21,991 --> 01:04:24,152
the discovery of that trap door
in the basement,

1108
01:04:24,227 --> 01:04:25,888
or the fact that I'd spilled
the beans to a first lifer.

1109
01:04:25,962 --> 01:04:31,093
...first lifer would be eaten for
merely assuming what you already know.

1110
01:04:31,267 --> 01:04:32,199
Really?

1111
01:04:32,268 --> 01:04:32,996
Yes.

1112
01:04:33,836 --> 01:04:40,298
Now, getting back to this voice,
are you sure you heard 'Rebecca? '

1113
01:04:42,078 --> 01:04:43,204
I'm pretty sure.

1114
01:04:44,046 --> 01:04:46,947
Are you sure it wasn't 'ricotta? '

1115
01:04:48,184 --> 01:04:50,618
Ricotta? Like the cheese?

1116
01:04:50,686 --> 01:04:51,277
Yes.

1117
01:04:51,754 --> 01:04:52,652
No.

1118
01:04:52,788 --> 01:04:55,780
Okay. I'm gonna do
a quick look-see around the room,

1119
01:04:55,858 --> 01:04:58,418
can you go get Henry and Otto
and bring them down here chop-chop?

1120
01:04:58,628 --> 01:04:59,219
Yeah.

1121
01:04:59,295 --> 01:05:00,057
Okay.

1122
01:05:00,830 --> 01:05:02,297
So where does it go?

1123
01:05:04,433 --> 01:05:05,365
Down.

1124
01:05:07,637 --> 01:05:08,399
Anything?

1125
01:05:09,372 --> 01:05:14,275
Yeah. Looks like a bunch of emails
between Mike and someone named Thomas.

1126
01:05:14,343 --> 01:05:16,243
Deleted, but not deleted.

1127
01:05:16,312 --> 01:05:16,778
Right.

1128
01:05:17,146 --> 01:05:18,078
Several of them mention

1129
01:05:18,147 --> 01:05:20,479
that Mike's supposed to be
researching something for this guy.

1130
01:05:21,183 --> 01:05:22,172
In one of the emails,

1131
01:05:23,886 --> 01:05:27,083
Thomas requests that Mike should
begin to administer a daily,

1132
01:05:27,156 --> 01:05:28,680
no more than half a gram per day.

1133
01:05:29,525 --> 01:05:32,187
Doesn't specifically mention
Turner poisoned, though.

1134
01:05:32,261 --> 01:05:33,159
When was that?

1135
01:05:34,230 --> 01:05:38,030
September 20th. Two months ago.

1136
01:05:43,839 --> 01:05:45,170
Excuse me, Turner?

1137
01:05:45,708 --> 01:05:49,303
Oliver. Here to urinate?
Pull up some porcelain.

1138
01:05:49,378 --> 01:05:52,176
No, thanks, I'm fine.
I was wondering if...

1139
01:05:52,248 --> 01:05:53,875
Is it a penis thing or something,
Oliver?

1140
01:05:53,950 --> 01:05:56,384
'Cause don't worry, I won't look.

1141
01:05:57,486 --> 01:05:59,283
It's a very compelling offer, sir.

1142
01:05:59,889 --> 01:06:04,053
But, uh, I wanted to know
if Mike set up the deal

1143
01:06:04,126 --> 01:06:06,253
to hire the productivity consultant?

1144
01:06:06,329 --> 01:06:07,023
The Frenchman?

1145
01:06:07,697 --> 01:06:08,664
The Frenchman?

1146
01:06:08,731 --> 01:06:09,823
Steven Long-dree?

1147
01:06:10,266 --> 01:06:11,130
Mike's baby?

1148
01:06:12,201 --> 01:06:15,864
Oh, I got this for you.

1149
01:06:16,505 --> 01:06:18,097
Had the Frenchman pick them up.

1150
01:06:20,776 --> 01:06:23,836
Keep an eye out for
those tricky little bastards.

1151
01:07:39,889 --> 01:07:41,857
Then a couple of weeks ago,
Thomas stopped writing.

1152
01:07:42,458 --> 01:07:43,584
And all of a sudden,

1153
01:07:43,893 --> 01:07:49,331
Mike starts getting very similar
sounding emails from Landry Ventures.

1154
01:07:50,800 --> 01:07:54,099
Steven. The thick plottens.

1155
01:08:02,111 --> 01:08:03,339
See anything you like?

1156
01:08:08,584 --> 01:08:11,883
You look a little tired.
Maybe you should take a nap.

1157
01:08:13,722 --> 01:08:15,451
Otto,
can we borrow you for just a moment?

1158
01:08:16,158 --> 01:08:16,954
Yes.

1159
01:08:22,598 --> 01:08:24,828
You really think you're going
to need the Buntline, Henry?

1160
01:08:25,301 --> 01:08:26,290
Sure hope not.

1161
01:08:34,877 --> 01:08:38,540
Cheese and crackers, Henry.
I nearly soiled my britches.

1162
01:08:39,281 --> 01:08:40,578
What are you doing down here?

1163
01:08:40,649 --> 01:08:43,641
Came down to get one of those
mothball files out of the archives.

1164
01:08:44,153 --> 01:08:46,986
Hey, what are you all doing down here
in the dark, anyway?

1165
01:08:48,958 --> 01:08:50,186
Care for a little adventure, Jeff?

1166
01:08:51,393 --> 01:08:54,055
No I would not. I would just as soon
get my file and go.

1167
01:08:54,130 --> 01:08:58,829
Besides, the last time I checked, trap
doors is supervisors' work, anyway.

1168
01:08:58,901 --> 01:09:00,129
Actually, I don't recall trap doors

1169
01:09:00,202 --> 01:09:02,830
being put in any of
the upper-level job descriptions.

1170
01:09:03,005 --> 01:09:05,405
Don't be a drag
on the supply chain here, Jeff.

1171
01:09:05,474 --> 01:09:06,907
I need you to take some ownership.

1172
01:09:07,076 --> 01:09:09,476
Come on. God almighty. Come on.

1173
01:09:13,482 --> 01:09:15,347
What is this? A sewer pipe?

1174
01:09:15,584 --> 01:09:17,381
Well, it seems to
run underneath the alleyway.

1175
01:09:17,987 --> 01:09:18,954
What's across the alley?

1176
01:09:19,221 --> 01:09:20,347
The Tamerline building.

1177
01:09:21,323 --> 01:09:24,952
Hey Waxy, this tunnel don't
look like it's up to municipal code.

1178
01:09:25,327 --> 01:09:26,919
Are you sure it's wise to cross over?

1179
01:09:26,996 --> 01:09:28,224
Shh, Jeff, come on.

1180
01:09:31,834 --> 01:09:33,199
Get some light on there.

1181
01:09:39,241 --> 01:09:41,175
I didn't know it
took two separate keys.

1182
01:09:41,377 --> 01:09:42,275
I'm never in the loop.

1183
01:09:43,112 --> 01:09:44,977
Well somebody is lying.

1184
01:09:45,614 --> 01:09:52,486
Now the question is, are you lying to
me, or has Turner been lying to you?

1185
01:09:53,589 --> 01:09:55,716
Now, we're gonna...

1186
01:09:55,791 --> 01:09:56,689
This is not good.

1187
01:09:58,093 --> 01:10:00,527
Go fetch Dr. Berman,
tell him it's time for the Rinse.

1188
01:10:01,263 --> 01:10:01,729
You sure?

1189
01:10:01,797 --> 01:10:02,957
Yeah, just go.

1190
01:10:03,399 --> 01:10:04,297
What the?

1191
01:10:04,366 --> 01:10:06,027
I can hear you in there.

1192
01:10:08,537 --> 01:10:09,663
Go, go, go!

1193
01:10:09,738 --> 01:10:14,198
You have exactly three seconds
to come into this room

1194
01:10:14,310 --> 01:10:18,940
before the next sound you hear will be
Bunyan's head exploding like a melon.

1195
01:10:20,816 --> 01:10:25,719
One, two...

1196
01:10:26,689 --> 01:10:27,815
Alright, Steven,

1197
01:10:29,558 --> 01:10:30,320
let him go.

1198
01:10:30,392 --> 01:10:34,385
Oh, right.
I'll do just that little thing.

1199
01:10:35,197 --> 01:10:36,596
Put down the gun or I'll kill him.

1200
01:10:36,665 --> 01:10:38,064
Now you know I can't do that.

1201
01:10:39,401 --> 01:10:42,928
If you kill Bunyan, you're dead.
It's that simple.

1202
01:10:43,572 --> 01:10:47,099
So, slicing his head off
is a bad negotiating tactic?

1203
01:10:47,643 --> 01:10:51,409
How about if I have something else
to bargain with.

1204
01:10:52,548 --> 01:10:53,446
What?

1205
01:10:53,515 --> 01:10:56,040
Not what, who.

1206
01:10:57,186 --> 01:10:58,517
Your co-workers.

1207
01:10:58,587 --> 01:10:59,076
Where are they?

1208
01:10:59,355 --> 01:11:03,052
Well they're fine,
they're just heavily sedated.

1209
01:11:03,359 --> 01:11:04,257
They're in the drawers.

1210
01:11:05,227 --> 01:11:06,455
I got him, Henry.

1211
01:11:28,117 --> 01:11:29,015
She's dead.

1212
01:11:29,485 --> 01:11:31,919
Emmitt was surprisingly tough.

1213
01:11:31,987 --> 01:11:34,979
It took me two hours
to get anything out of him.

1214
01:11:35,057 --> 01:11:36,991
But Rebecca,

1215
01:11:37,626 --> 01:11:39,423
I take my hat off to Rebecca.

1216
01:11:39,895 --> 01:11:41,487
She gave me nothing.

1217
01:11:42,164 --> 01:11:46,464
Absolutely nothing,
and I am persuasive.

1218
01:11:49,004 --> 01:11:50,062
Give me the gun.

1219
01:11:51,607 --> 01:11:52,437
Jeff.

1220
01:12:00,749 --> 01:12:04,617
Will you look at that?
I have been looking all over for that.

1221
01:12:04,753 --> 01:12:07,779
That is the power
of positive thinking.

1222
01:12:08,390 --> 01:12:09,414
Go ahead, get me that key.

1223
01:12:13,896 --> 01:12:15,295
Get out of here, get out of here.

1224
01:12:15,364 --> 01:12:16,126
Oh, she's getting away.

1225
01:12:26,475 --> 01:12:29,410
That's the stuff, Jeff.
Now go get the girl.

1226
01:12:37,086 --> 01:12:39,111
Excellent effort, Granberry.

1227
01:12:39,188 --> 01:12:40,280
I knew you had it in you.

1228
01:12:41,790 --> 01:12:42,950
You see her?

1229
01:12:43,025 --> 01:12:45,016
No.
Can't see a blasted thing down here.

1230
01:12:45,094 --> 01:12:47,528
But if she's still in here,
she'll feel this!

1231
01:12:48,697 --> 01:12:52,895
Ah! God almighty! I'm hit.

1232
01:12:53,936 --> 01:12:58,032
Ricochets are a freakishly
random event, Jeff. Shake it off.

1233
01:12:58,407 --> 01:13:01,672
Come on up here, roll one of
those barrels over the trap door.

1234
01:13:01,977 --> 01:13:03,342
We don't want any more visitors.

1235
01:13:03,712 --> 01:13:04,872
Bad news.

1236
01:13:04,947 --> 01:13:06,505
I love his can-do attitude.

1237
01:13:06,849 --> 01:13:08,282
This is gonna hurt a lot.

1238
01:13:12,454 --> 01:13:16,015
So this is the Rinse?
How long's it usually take?

1239
01:13:16,258 --> 01:13:18,055
He should feel something
in about five minutes.

1240
01:13:19,862 --> 01:13:21,386
Can we leave him
in your capable hands?

1241
01:13:21,463 --> 01:13:22,293
Of course.

1242
01:13:22,364 --> 01:13:23,194
Let's go, guys.

1243
01:13:47,189 --> 01:13:49,987
Goodbye, sweet Henry.

1244
01:13:53,896 --> 01:13:57,388
Welcome to my hostile takeover.

1245
01:13:58,867 --> 01:14:01,097
But it can still be
a win-win situation.

1246
01:14:01,503 --> 01:14:03,528
You want your lifestyle to continue,

1247
01:14:04,706 --> 01:14:06,333
I want the Nether Stone.

1248
01:14:07,676 --> 01:14:10,236
I don't see
why we both can't get what we want.

1249
01:14:10,412 --> 01:14:11,572
You're one of us?

1250
01:14:12,147 --> 01:14:13,739
He's not one of us.

1251
01:14:14,216 --> 01:14:21,122
You're both right. I am a Nether Man,
but I am not one of you.

1252
01:14:21,623 --> 01:14:28,461
I was not randomly generated by a cosmic
crap shoot of genes and chromosomes.

1253
01:14:28,764 --> 01:14:33,929
No fellas. I was chosen.

1254
01:14:34,536 --> 01:14:37,903
It was Garfield who hit
on the idea of a heart transplant.

1255
01:14:38,106 --> 01:14:40,370
Let's say I were in agreement
with this, gentlemen.

1256
01:14:40,442 --> 01:14:41,966
Where in the name of Laura Keen

1257
01:14:42,044 --> 01:14:44,638
would we find a willing candidate
for such a procedure?

1258
01:14:44,913 --> 01:14:47,575
I know a man, sir,
whose own heart has failed him.

1259
01:14:47,649 --> 01:14:49,640
This man will die
before the year is out.

1260
01:14:49,785 --> 01:14:51,719
Do you know his whereabouts
at the present time?

1261
01:14:53,088 --> 01:14:55,852
Watson, come here. I want you.

1262
01:14:58,927 --> 01:14:59,859
Yes, Mr. Bell?

1263
01:15:01,430 --> 01:15:05,526
Mr. Bell, you're a bright man.

1264
01:15:06,768 --> 01:15:14,197
I would consider any favor granted to
my Nether Folk a favor in my own pocket.

1265
01:15:14,276 --> 01:15:17,268
I'll do my level best, Mr. President.

1266
01:15:17,880 --> 01:15:20,849
I never thought I'd be
giving my heart to another man.

1267
01:15:23,652 --> 01:15:24,846
Buck up, son.

1268
01:15:25,921 --> 01:15:27,946
That may be
my very last humorous remark.

1269
01:15:28,590 --> 01:15:29,750
Why are you doing this?

1270
01:15:31,460 --> 01:15:35,590
Turner has brainwashed
you all into mediocrity.

1271
01:15:37,432 --> 01:15:42,961
At Berm-Tech,
all you run is a cubicle.

1272
01:15:44,273 --> 01:15:45,570
Don't you want more?

1273
01:15:45,641 --> 01:15:46,369
Like what?

1274
01:15:46,775 --> 01:15:49,903
To live amongst
the humans as their superiors.

1275
01:15:52,014 --> 01:15:57,452
And the more Nether Stone you have,
the more powerful you become.

1276
01:15:58,020 --> 01:16:00,045
That's how you're able to walk
in the sunlight.

1277
01:16:00,322 --> 01:16:01,721
That's right.

1278
01:16:03,825 --> 01:16:06,487
Berm-Tech is going to be expanding.

1279
01:16:11,266 --> 01:16:15,965
And those that don't get the ax
will receive greater benefits,

1280
01:16:16,438 --> 01:16:18,736
greater freedom to go outside,

1281
01:16:19,508 --> 01:16:22,773
an incredible retirement package.

1282
01:16:23,178 --> 01:16:24,611
I got my...

1283
01:16:24,846 --> 01:16:26,575
Oh, wait, is that bullet still in you?

1284
01:16:26,648 --> 01:16:28,047
Well, I'm not sure.

1285
01:16:28,116 --> 01:16:30,983
It has gone straight through.
You are fine.

1286
01:16:31,386 --> 01:16:33,547
Have crackers and a ginger ale.

1287
01:16:34,923 --> 01:16:38,359
Can do, can do.

1288
01:16:38,427 --> 01:16:42,454
Granberry,
we are not more evil than you.

1289
01:16:43,298 --> 01:16:48,395
We are rising above your way
of survival. At least trying to.

1290
01:16:48,537 --> 01:16:50,198
Oh, I see, yeah.

1291
01:16:50,973 --> 01:16:54,739
You're enlightened.
And I'm a monster, right?

1292
01:16:55,744 --> 01:17:00,204
You forget, we both eat people.

1293
01:17:00,515 --> 01:17:01,641
Berman, what is going on?

1294
01:17:02,084 --> 01:17:04,712
Take it easy, Turner. Just lie down.

1295
01:17:04,786 --> 01:17:07,118
Listen, Mike Yarrow can't be trusted,

1296
01:17:07,489 --> 01:17:10,788
he's only here to steal the stone.

1297
01:17:14,730 --> 01:17:16,254
I killed Mike, didn't I?

1298
01:17:17,099 --> 01:17:17,963
Yes.

1299
01:17:25,240 --> 01:17:26,502
This is the Rinse, isn't it?

1300
01:17:35,283 --> 01:17:39,083
Maybe, maybe we should go outside
and try the front door.

1301
01:17:39,154 --> 01:17:41,281
Oh, into the daylight? Are you crazy?

1302
01:17:41,757 --> 01:17:44,385
How else are we supposed
to get into that building?

1303
01:17:45,761 --> 01:17:49,026
Hey, we're brainstorming here guys,
there are no bad ideas.

1304
01:17:49,631 --> 01:17:49,995
Follow me.

1305
01:17:52,634 --> 01:17:57,799
Jeff, would you please go make sure
that the barrel has not been moved?

1306
01:17:58,306 --> 01:17:59,500
Can do, captain.

1307
01:18:05,814 --> 01:18:08,578
This is not looking good for you guys.

1308
01:18:17,826 --> 01:18:19,225
Oh, boss?

1309
01:18:22,097 --> 01:18:26,761
You humans are such a pain in the ass.

1310
01:18:27,202 --> 01:18:28,191
No, no!

1311
01:18:34,242 --> 01:18:38,508
Oh, oh, what are you going to do?

1312
01:18:39,147 --> 01:18:40,671
You're going to shoot me
with an empty gun?

1313
01:18:41,850 --> 01:18:48,949
Here. It's a six shooter.
Count 'em out. Henry, you...

1314
01:18:50,625 --> 01:18:58,794
Ow. Jeff shot himself, and then
three shots in your lovely girlfriend.

1315
01:19:10,312 --> 01:19:12,678
That's a piss poor attitude.

1316
01:19:14,049 --> 01:19:17,450
You are not a team player.

1317
01:19:27,062 --> 01:19:30,657
Okay, okay, okay, come on.

1318
01:19:30,732 --> 01:19:32,029
No, no, no, no, no.

1319
01:19:32,100 --> 01:19:34,034
Come on. Come here.

1320
01:19:34,102 --> 01:19:37,128
I've never seen anyone stabbed
to death with a gun before.

1321
01:19:37,939 --> 01:19:41,841
I'm afraid she won't make it
through the night, Otto. I'm sorry.

1322
01:19:43,912 --> 01:19:45,573
You know,
I almost hoped she was one of us.

1323
01:19:48,016 --> 01:19:51,577
Turner's last recruit,
so a few bullets would be no big deal.

1324
01:19:52,587 --> 01:19:55,852
She's just flesh and blood,
nothing more than that.

1325
01:19:58,994 --> 01:20:01,758
Obviously she's much more than
that figuratively speaking,

1326
01:20:01,830 --> 01:20:04,663
but from a purely
physiological standpoint,

1327
01:20:04,733 --> 01:20:09,067
she's flesh and, uh, yeah, blood.

1328
01:20:10,038 --> 01:20:11,335
I'll just be over here.

1329
01:20:14,709 --> 01:20:19,112
Otto, Turner wants to see you.

1330
01:20:20,715 --> 01:20:23,582
Here you go, boysenberry.

1331
01:20:31,760 --> 01:20:33,694
I've had a lot to process today.

1332
01:20:34,429 --> 01:20:43,997
But nothing supersedes the importance
of keeping Berm-Tech Industries intact.

1333
01:20:44,673 --> 01:20:48,404
After Rebecca and Henry,

1334
01:20:48,810 --> 01:20:54,077
that Bunyan Pritchett
is our go-to guy.

1335
01:20:55,417 --> 01:20:58,580
And that leaves several managerial
positions open.

1336
01:21:00,322 --> 01:21:03,849
And I would appreciate it
if you would take one of those.

1337
01:21:04,893 --> 01:21:06,087
I'll do my level best.

1338
01:21:06,328 --> 01:21:08,023
I know you will.

1339
01:21:09,764 --> 01:21:11,527
I've already spoken with Bunyan.

1340
01:21:13,301 --> 01:21:17,533
And he now has the set of files
that contains everything.

1341
01:21:17,606 --> 01:21:23,272
Our holdings, our history,
and the stone.

1342
01:21:25,447 --> 01:21:28,905
The stone wasn't in the freezer.

1343
01:21:29,885 --> 01:21:32,615
I know. It was my little secret.

1344
01:21:34,489 --> 01:21:36,821
Why lie to us about it?

1345
01:21:37,459 --> 01:21:41,555
The exact reason
that we're in this situation, Otto.

1346
01:21:44,766 --> 01:21:45,755
Greed.

1347
01:21:47,102 --> 01:21:49,036
The stone is like a drug,

1348
01:21:49,571 --> 01:21:53,098
I mean, that's why it had to be
broken up in the first place.

1349
01:21:54,175 --> 01:21:56,234
So we do have Nether Stone.

1350
01:21:57,412 --> 01:21:58,572
Yes.

1351
01:21:59,881 --> 01:22:05,478
Mike and Jeff spent three years
searching for it. Where is it?

1352
01:22:05,553 --> 01:22:07,350
It's in a lot of little pieces.

1353
01:22:08,690 --> 01:22:14,925
And every night it's usually
in the last place that you would look.

1354
01:22:18,600 --> 01:22:19,498
The hideous lamps.

1355
01:22:23,038 --> 01:22:27,338
It's so funny. It, it seems
that people often think about

1356
01:22:27,409 --> 01:22:35,009
how they would live differently
if they only had a day, or a week.

1357
01:22:36,384 --> 01:22:37,681
They don't ever stop to think about

1358
01:22:37,752 --> 01:22:42,587
how they would change
if they had to live forever.

1359
01:22:44,259 --> 01:22:47,888
And now there is one more thing
I want to do.

1360
01:23:01,509 --> 01:23:04,706
Shh, shh. Don't

1361
01:23:11,886 --> 01:23:15,287
So Turner,
like President Garfield before him,

1362
01:23:16,124 --> 01:23:18,285
made the ultimate sacrifice.

1363
01:23:19,995 --> 01:23:22,395
His leadership carried us
through our darkest times.

1364
01:23:24,032 --> 01:23:26,500
It'll be up to us
now to step into the light.

1365
01:23:27,435 --> 01:23:28,402
All of us.

1366
01:23:29,938 --> 01:23:34,068
Okay, so I can see that our
other meeting is about to begin,

1367
01:23:34,142 --> 01:23:38,169
so as long as your brief, I'd be happy
to take any questions at his time.

1368
01:23:38,513 --> 01:23:39,377
Just one.

1369
01:23:40,682 --> 01:23:42,172
How long did it take you

1370
01:23:42,250 --> 01:23:45,219
to prepare this little Nether Beast
In Training presentation?

1371
01:23:47,188 --> 01:23:49,452
About a hundred and eight years.

1372
01:23:54,062 --> 01:23:57,759
So, that's the way the organization
will look beginning Monday.

1373
01:23:58,566 --> 01:24:00,124
There's been a lot of changes,

1374
01:24:00,201 --> 01:24:02,567
and we haven't done a re-org
in quite a long stretch.

1375
01:24:03,304 --> 01:24:07,468
We're dead serious about relaxing
the policy on outdoor excursions.

1376
01:24:10,612 --> 01:24:12,239
Made possible in part

1377
01:24:12,447 --> 01:24:16,110
by a mother load of Nether Stone
involuntarily donated

1378
01:24:16,184 --> 01:24:18,175
by the late Steven P.D. Landry.

1379
01:24:21,756 --> 01:24:24,623
But give us a couple of weeks
to get things straightened out.

1380
01:24:24,793 --> 01:24:28,229
I'd do a lap around the room for Q&A,
but this is a large group.

1381
01:24:28,396 --> 01:24:30,956
And besides, it's time for lunch.

1382
01:24:31,766 --> 01:24:35,566
So let's move in a safe and orderly
fashion down to the dining area.

1383
01:24:46,681 --> 01:24:47,841
Long meeting, huh?

1384
01:24:48,316 --> 01:24:50,007
I didn't think lunch
would ever get here.

1385
01:24:52,854 --> 01:24:53,616
You hungry?

1386
01:24:55,557 --> 01:24:56,854
Starving.

1387
01:25:08,403 --> 01:25:10,530
END

1388
